<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880517-0142 </DOCNO><HL> Diagnostic/Retrieval To Acquire Photronics </HL><SO> </SO><CO> DRSA PHOT </CO><IN> TNM </IN><DATELINE> OAKLAND, N.J.  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Military contractor Diagnostic/Retrieval Systems Inc. said it is acquiring Photronics Corp., another military supplier, for $14.9 million.    The companies said their directors have approved a definitive merger agreement that calls for Diagnostic/Retrieval to pay $6.75 a share for all of Photronics' common stock outstanding, and $3.75 for its warrants. Photronics has 2,052,970 common shares and 276,500 warrants outstanding. Diagnostic/Retrieval also was given an option to buy as many as 410,594 of Photronics's authorized, unissued common shares.    Diagnostic/Retrieval designs and produces computer systems, primarily for the Navy; Photronics produces allied products, mainly for the Army. Photronics, based in Hauppauge, N.Y., said John McGovern agreed to remain as chairman of the company, which will become a unit of Diagnostic/Retrieval.    In yesterday's national over-the-counter trading, Photronics shares closed at $6.25, up 12.5 cents. </TEXT></DOC>